   <conbody>
      <section class="- topic/section ">
         <sectiondiv class="- topic/sectiondiv ">
            <hazardstatement conref="../Library/Warnings_Library_0000325173.dita#war_lib/neutral-current-exceed-ampacity"
                             platform="PxW WxW"
                             class="+ topic/note hazard-d/hazardstatement ">
               <messagepanel class="+ topic/ul hazard-d/messagepanel ">
                  <typeofhazard class="+ topic/li hazard-d/typeofhazard "/>
                  <howtoavoid class="+ topic/li hazard-d/howtoavoid "/>
               </messagepanel>
            </hazardstatement>
            <p class="- topic/p ">The load cables must be installed
and connected according to the maximum allowable load. Always check
that the connected load does not exceed the maximum rated capacity
of the system<ph platform="PxW WxW" class="- topic/ph "> and is within the specified power
factor (cos phi)</ph>. </p>
            <note platform="PxW WxW" class="- topic/note ">Be aware that
a three-phase system can have a single-phase load with the load connected
between phase and neutral.</note>
            <p class="- topic/p ">When connecting the load consider
that:<ul class="- topic/ul ">
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p class="- topic/p ">All wiring must comply with all applicable local and/or national
electrical codes</p>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p class="- topic/p ">The cables and connections are according to the maximum allowed
load, see the <i class="+ topic/ph hi-d/i ">Technical Data</i>.</p>
                  </li>
                  <li platform="PxW WxW" class="- topic/li ">
                     <p class="- topic/p ">For three-phase systems with non-linear
loads, for example SMPS, make sure that the neutral current does not
exceed the rated ampacity of the conductor.</p>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p class="- topic/p ">The person carrying out the work must be an authorized electrician.</p>
                  </li>
               </ul>
            </p>
         </sectiondiv>
      </section>
      <section platform="PxW WxW" class="- topic/section ">
         <title class="- topic/title ">Neutral Conductor at the Output</title>
         <sectiondiv class="- topic/sectiondiv ">
            <p class="- topic/p ">It is recommended to connect the output neutral to
earth. It might be necessary to install a bypass transformer with
galvanic isolation to connect the output neutral to earth. Refer to
the <i class="+ topic/ph hi-d/i ">Circuit Diagram</i> of the system and always follow local and/or
national regulations.</p>
         </sectiondiv>
      </section>
      <section class="- topic/section ">
         <title class="- topic/title ">External Protection at the Output</title>
         <sectiondiv class="- topic/sectiondiv ">
            <p class="- topic/p ">To ensure selectivity between the internal fuses/MCCBs and the
distribution fuses/MCCBs, the maximum fuse nominal current (rated
circuit breaker current) at the load output is limited.</p>
         </sectiondiv>
      </section>
      <section class="- topic/section ">
         <title class="- topic/title ">Busbar Circuit Breaker at the Output</title>
         <sectiondiv class="- topic/sectiondiv ">
            <p class="- topic/p ">When using circuit breakers between the output busbar and the
consumer it is recommended to use circuit breakers with a tripping
curve and rating so that the selectivity is still provided.</p>
            <note class="- topic/note ">The voltage drop between the system and the consumer should be maximum
3%.</note>
         </sectiondiv>
      </section>
